<div class="entry-content"><div class="wprm-recipe wprm-recipe-snippet wprm-recipe-template-tracys-custom-buttons"><a href="#recipe" data-recipe="5858" style="color: #ffffff;background-color: #d7d7d7;border-color: #d7d7d7;border-radius: 3px;padding: 5px 8px;" class="wprm-recipe-jump wprm-recipe-link wprm-jump-to-recipe-shortcode wprm-block-text-normal wprm-recipe-jump-inline-button wprm-recipe-link-inline-button wprm-color-accent"><span class="wprm-recipe-icon wprm-recipe-jump-icon"><svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" width="16" height="16" viewBox="0 0 24 24"><g class="nc-icon-wrapper" fill="#ffffff"><path data-color="color-2" d="M9,2h6c0.6,0,1-0.4,1-1s-0.4-1-1-1H9C8.4,0,8,0.4,8,1S8.4,2,9,2z"></path> <path fill="#ffffff" d="M16,11V5c0-0.6-0.4-1-1-1H9C8.4,4,8,4.4,8,5v6H1.9L12,23.6L22.1,11H16z"></path></g></svg></span> Jump to Recipe</a>
<a href="#recipe-video" data-recipe="5858" style="color: #ffffff;background-color: #d7d7d7;border-color: #d7d7d7;border-radius: 3px;padding: 5px 8px;" class="wprm-recipe-jump-video wprm-recipe-link wprm-jump-to-video-shortcode wprm-block-text-normal wprm-recipe-jump-video-inline-button wprm-recipe-link-inline-button wprm-color-accent"><span class="wprm-recipe-icon wprm-recipe-jump-video-icon"><svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" width="16" height="16" viewBox="0 0 24 24"><g class="nc-icon-wrapper" fill="#ffffff"><path fill="#ffffff" d="M22,8H2C1.448,8,1,8.447,1,9v14c0,0.553,0.448,1,1,1h20c0.552,0,1-0.447,1-1V9C23,8.447,22.552,8,22,8z M9,20v-8l7,4L9,20z"></path> <rect data-color="color-2" x="0.001" y="2.111" transform="matrix(0.9798 -0.1999 0.1999 0.9798 -0.4028 2.2323)" width="21.701" height="2"></rect></g></svg></span> Jump to Video</a>
<a href="https://www.ohmyfoodrecipes.com/wprm_print/braised-beef-and-radish" style="color: #ffffff;background-color: #d7d7d7;border-color: #d7d7d7;border-radius: 3px;padding: 5px 8px;" class="wprm-recipe-print wprm-recipe-link wprm-print-recipe-shortcode wprm-block-text-normal wprm-recipe-print-inline-button wprm-recipe-link-inline-button wprm-color-accent" data-recipe-id="5858" data-template="" target="_blank" rel="nofollow"><span class="wprm-recipe-icon wprm-recipe-print-icon"><svg width="16px" height="16px" viewBox="0 0 24 24" version="1.1" xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" xmlns:xlink="http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink"><g stroke="none" stroke-width="1" fill="none" fill-rule="evenodd"><g fill="#ffffff"><g><path d="M17.5454,0.0005 C18.2904,0.0005 18.9004,0.6105 18.9004,1.3565 L18.9004,1.3565 L18.9004,4.9445 L21.9904,4.9445 C23.0954,4.9445 24.0004,5.8485 24.0004,6.9535 L24.0004,6.9535 L24.0004,17.2415 C24.0004,18.3465 23.0954,19.2505 21.9904,19.2505 L21.9904,19.2505 L19.8414,19.2505 L19.8414,22.2795 C19.8414,23.1725 19.1104,23.9035 18.2174,23.9035 L18.2174,23.9035 L5.7834,23.9035 C4.8894,23.9035 4.1594,23.1725 4.1594,22.2795 L4.1594,22.2795 L4.1594,19.2505 L2.0104,19.2505 C0.9044,19.2505 0.0004,18.3465 0.0004,17.2415 L0.0004,17.2415 L0.0004,6.9535 C0.0004,5.8485 0.9044,4.9445 2.0104,4.9445 L2.0104,4.9445 L5.0984,4.9445 L5.0984,1.3565 C5.0984,0.6105 5.7094,0.0005 6.4554,0.0005 L6.4554,0.0005 Z M17.8414,15.5975 L6.1594,15.5975 L6.1594,21.9035 L17.8414,21.9035 L17.8414,15.5975 Z M21.9904,6.9445 L2.0104,6.9445 L2.0004,17.2415 L4.1594,17.2425 L4.1594,15.2215 C4.1594,14.3285 4.8894,13.5975 5.7834,13.5975 L5.7834,13.5975 L18.2174,13.5975 C19.1104,13.5975 19.8414,14.3285 19.8414,15.2215 L19.8414,15.2215 L19.8414,17.2495 L21.9904,17.2505 L22.0004,6.9535 L21.9904,6.9445 Z M6.1632,9.1318 C6.7902,9.1318 7.2992,9.6408 7.2992,10.2678 C7.2992,10.8948 6.7902,11.4028 6.1632,11.4028 L6.1632,11.4028 L5.0992,11.4028 C4.4722,11.4028 3.9632,10.8948 3.9632,10.2678 C3.9632,9.6408 4.4722,9.1318 5.0992,9.1318 L5.0992,9.1318 Z M16.6304,2.2715 L7.3704,2.2715 L7.3704,4.6845 L16.6304,4.6845 L16.6304,2.2715 Z"></path></g></g></g></svg></span> Print Recipe</a></div><span id="dpsp-post-content-markup" data-image-pin-it="true"></span><p class="p1">Delicious Asian Chinese flavor beef stew with radish instant pot is one of my comfort foods. This Cantonese style Chinese braised beef brisket and daikon instant pot recipe takes around 2 hours. Wanna know how to make this tasty dish? See the details and video below.</p>
<p>Love Asian food? Check out these <a href="https://www.ohmyfoodrecipes.com/ma-yi-shang-shu/">ma yi shang shu</a>, <a href="https://www.ohmyfoodrecipes.com/gyudon/">gyudon beef bowl</a>, <a href="https://www.ohmyfoodrecipes.com/laksa-noodle-soup/">laksa noodle soup</a> recipes.</p>
<p><img data-perfmatters-preload decoding="async" fetchpriority="high" class="aligncenter wp-image-5843 size-large" src="https://www.ohmyfoodrecipes.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/03/braised-beef-and-radish-front-659x1024.jpg" alt="Asian beef stew braised beef and radish in a brown pot " width="610" height="948" srcset="https://www.ohmyfoodrecipes.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/03/braised-beef-and-radish-front-659x1024.jpg 659w, https://www.ohmyfoodrecipes.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/03/braised-beef-and-radish-front-322x500.jpg 322w, https://www.ohmyfoodrecipes.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/03/braised-beef-and-radish-front-768x1194.jpg 768w, https://www.ohmyfoodrecipes.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/03/braised-beef-and-radish-front-988x1536.jpg 988w, https://www.ohmyfoodrecipes.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/03/braised-beef-and-radish-front.jpg 1200w" sizes="(max-width: 610px) 100vw, 610px" data-pin-media="https://www.ohmyfoodrecipes.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/03/braised-beef-and-radish-front.jpg"></p>
<h2 class="p1">What is braised beef and radish?</h2>
<p class="p1">Cantonese style braised beef and radish is a classic and famous Chinese dish. Not only the beef is soft and tender, but also the daikon is juicy. Also, it often serves with rice or noodles. For example, <a href="https://www.ohmyfoodrecipes.com/braised-beef-ho-fun-noodle-soup/">braised beef ho fun noodle soup</a> is one of the popular noodle soups.</p>
<h2 class="p1">Instant pot braised beef brisket and daikon</h2>
<p class="p1">Braised beef and daikon normally takes a few hours slowly cook them over the stove, so the meat will be tender and juicy. Some people like to use slow cooker or instant pot to make this Asian beef stew.</p>
<p class="p1">Personally, I love to use instant pot pressure cooker to make this Chinese beef brisket recipe because it is faster and can keep the meat soft and moist. Besides, daikon soak in the sauce makes it amazing delicious!</p>
<p class="p1">The previous <a href="https://www.ohmyfoodrecipes.com/braised-beef-ho-fun-noodle-soup/">braised beef ho fun noodle soup</a> recipe, I use the same ingredients but different ways to cook them. I put all the ingredients into instant pot and manual for 60 minutes and natural release. This way is so easy and less work. But, daikon will be softer.</p>
<p class="p1">Some people don&rsquo;t like radish too soft. Therefore, this time I showed another way to cook Chinese braised brisket beef&nbsp; in pressure cooker that radish will not too soft, yet it cooks through and juicy.</p>
<h2 class="p1">What are the ingredients in Chinese braised beef and turnip?</h2>
<p class="p1">I try to keep it simple. The main ingredients are beef, daikon, ginger, garlic, cloves, star anise and green onion. Often people like to use brisket beef. However, I like to use beef chunks roast boneless because it is cheaper, leaner and easier to find at the regular grocery store. Brisket beef is hard to find near where I live.</p>
<p><img decoding="async" class="aligncenter wp-image-5850 perfmatters-lazy" src="data:image/svg+xml,%3Csvg%20xmlns=&#039;http://www.w3.org/2000/svg&#039;%20width=&#039;850&#039;%20height=&#039;567&#039;%20viewBox=&#039;0%200%20850%20567&#039;%3E%3C/svg%3E" alt="Asian beef stew Chinese beef brisket ingredients" width="850" height="567" data-pin-media="https://www.ohmyfoodrecipes.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/03/Braised-beef-rasidh-ingredients.jpg" data-src="https://www.ohmyfoodrecipes.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/03/Braised-beef-rasidh-ingredients-1024x684.jpg" data-srcset="https://www.ohmyfoodrecipes.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/03/Braised-beef-rasidh-ingredients-1024x684.jpg 1024w, https://www.ohmyfoodrecipes.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/03/Braised-beef-rasidh-ingredients-500x334.jpg 500w, https://www.ohmyfoodrecipes.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/03/Braised-beef-rasidh-ingredients-768x513.jpg 768w, https://www.ohmyfoodrecipes.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/03/Braised-beef-rasidh-ingredients.jpg 1200w" data-sizes="(max-width: 850px) 100vw, 850px" /><noscript><img decoding="async" class="aligncenter wp-image-5850" src="https://www.ohmyfoodrecipes.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/03/Braised-beef-rasidh-ingredients-1024x684.jpg" alt="Asian beef stew Chinese beef brisket ingredients" width="850" height="567" srcset="https://www.ohmyfoodrecipes.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/03/Braised-beef-rasidh-ingredients-1024x684.jpg 1024w, https://www.ohmyfoodrecipes.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/03/Braised-beef-rasidh-ingredients-500x334.jpg 500w, https://www.ohmyfoodrecipes.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/03/Braised-beef-rasidh-ingredients-768x513.jpg 768w, https://www.ohmyfoodrecipes.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/03/Braised-beef-rasidh-ingredients.jpg 1200w" sizes="(max-width: 850px) 100vw, 850px" data-pin-media="https://www.ohmyfoodrecipes.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/03/Braised-beef-rasidh-ingredients.jpg"></noscript></p>
<h2 class="p1">Cooking tips for how to make instant pot Asian beef stew:</h2>
<ul>
<li class="p1">Wash, cut beef and radish into chunks</li>
<li class="p1">Add ginger, garlic, clove, star anise, beef brisket or beef roast into pressure cooker, then add the sauce and mix them well. Manual for 45 minutes at high pressure and natural release.</li>
<li class="p1">After that, add daikon mix them with sauce and beef and manual for 15 minutes at high pressure and natural release pressure.</li>
</ul>
<h2>FAQs:</h2>
<h3 class="p1">What kind of beef do you use?</h3>
<p class="p1">Often people like to use brisket beef. However, I like to use beef chunk roast boneless because it is cheaper, leaner and easier to find at the regular grocery store. Brisket beef is hard to find near where I live.</p>
<h3 class="p1">How do you handle the beef brisket or beef chunk roast?</h3>
<p class="p1">Some people like to boil them to remove oil and blood. But, I normally skip this step and use a strainer to remove fat after cooking. So, the sauce won&rsquo;t be too oily.</p>
<h2 class="p1">Instructions for how to make instant pot braised beef brisket and daikon:</h2>
<p>1. Wash, peel off radish skin and cut them into chunks. Then, set them aside.&nbsp;</p>
<p><img decoding="async" class="aligncenter wp-image-5849 perfmatters-lazy" src="data:image/svg+xml,%3Csvg%20xmlns=&#039;http://www.w3.org/2000/svg&#039;%20width=&#039;850&#039;%20height=&#039;567&#039;%20viewBox=&#039;0%200%20850%20567&#039;%3E%3C/svg%3E" alt="daikon cut into chunks" width="850" height="567" data-pin-media="https://www.ohmyfoodrecipes.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/03/radish-cut-into-chunks.jpg" data-src="https://www.ohmyfoodrecipes.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/03/radish-cut-into-chunks-1024x684.jpg" data-srcset="https://www.ohmyfoodrecipes.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/03/radish-cut-into-chunks-1024x684.jpg 1024w, https://www.ohmyfoodrecipes.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/03/radish-cut-into-chunks-500x334.jpg 500w, https://www.ohmyfoodrecipes.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/03/radish-cut-into-chunks-768x513.jpg 768w, https://www.ohmyfoodrecipes.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/03/radish-cut-into-chunks.jpg 1200w" data-sizes="(max-width: 850px) 100vw, 850px" /><noscript><img decoding="async" class="aligncenter wp-image-5849" src="https://www.ohmyfoodrecipes.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/03/radish-cut-into-chunks-1024x684.jpg" alt="daikon cut into chunks" width="850" height="567" srcset="https://www.ohmyfoodrecipes.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/03/radish-cut-into-chunks-1024x684.jpg 1024w, https://www.ohmyfoodrecipes.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/03/radish-cut-into-chunks-500x334.jpg 500w, https://www.ohmyfoodrecipes.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/03/radish-cut-into-chunks-768x513.jpg 768w, https://www.ohmyfoodrecipes.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/03/radish-cut-into-chunks.jpg 1200w" sizes="(max-width: 850px) 100vw, 850px" data-pin-media="https://www.ohmyfoodrecipes.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/03/radish-cut-into-chunks.jpg"></noscript></p>
<p>2. Wash and cut beef roast into chunks.</p>
<p><img decoding="async" class="aligncenter wp-image-5846 perfmatters-lazy" src="data:image/svg+xml,%3Csvg%20xmlns=&#039;http://www.w3.org/2000/svg&#039;%20width=&#039;850&#039;%20height=&#039;567&#039;%20viewBox=&#039;0%200%20850%20567&#039;%3E%3C/svg%3E" alt="beef roast cut into chunks" width="850" height="567" data-pin-media="https://www.ohmyfoodrecipes.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/03/beef-cut-into-chunks.jpg" data-src="https://www.ohmyfoodrecipes.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/03/beef-cut-into-chunks-1024x684.jpg" data-srcset="https://www.ohmyfoodrecipes.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/03/beef-cut-into-chunks-1024x684.jpg 1024w, https://www.ohmyfoodrecipes.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/03/beef-cut-into-chunks-500x334.jpg 500w, https://www.ohmyfoodrecipes.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/03/beef-cut-into-chunks-768x513.jpg 768w, https://www.ohmyfoodrecipes.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/03/beef-cut-into-chunks.jpg 1200w" data-sizes="(max-width: 850px) 100vw, 850px" /><noscript><img decoding="async" class="aligncenter wp-image-5846" src="https://www.ohmyfoodrecipes.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/03/beef-cut-into-chunks-1024x684.jpg" alt="beef roast cut into chunks" width="850" height="567" srcset="https://www.ohmyfoodrecipes.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/03/beef-cut-into-chunks-1024x684.jpg 1024w, https://www.ohmyfoodrecipes.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/03/beef-cut-into-chunks-500x334.jpg 500w, https://www.ohmyfoodrecipes.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/03/beef-cut-into-chunks-768x513.jpg 768w, https://www.ohmyfoodrecipes.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/03/beef-cut-into-chunks.jpg 1200w" sizes="(max-width: 850px) 100vw, 850px" data-pin-media="https://www.ohmyfoodrecipes.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/03/beef-cut-into-chunks.jpg"></noscript></p>
<p>3. After that, put 4 cloves of garlic, 5 slices of ginger, 5 pieces of star anise, 6 pieces of clove and beef roast. Next, add ½ teaspoon of salt, 3 tablespoons of soy sauce, 3 tablespoons of oyster sauce, 2 tablespoons of brown sugar and 1 cup of water. Mix them well. Close the lid and vent, then push manual button adjust time to 45 minutes at high pressure and nature release pressure.&nbsp;</p>
<p><img decoding="async" class="aligncenter wp-image-5847 perfmatters-lazy" src="data:image/svg+xml,%3Csvg%20xmlns=&#039;http://www.w3.org/2000/svg&#039;%20width=&#039;850&#039;%20height=&#039;567&#039;%20viewBox=&#039;0%200%20850%20567&#039;%3E%3C/svg%3E" alt="beef and sauce into instant pot" width="850" height="567" data-pin-media="https://www.ohmyfoodrecipes.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/03/beef-in-instant-pot.jpg" data-src="https://www.ohmyfoodrecipes.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/03/beef-in-instant-pot-1024x684.jpg" data-srcset="https://www.ohmyfoodrecipes.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/03/beef-in-instant-pot-1024x684.jpg 1024w, https://www.ohmyfoodrecipes.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/03/beef-in-instant-pot-500x334.jpg 500w, https://www.ohmyfoodrecipes.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/03/beef-in-instant-pot-768x513.jpg 768w, https://www.ohmyfoodrecipes.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/03/beef-in-instant-pot.jpg 1200w" data-sizes="(max-width: 850px) 100vw, 850px" /><noscript><img decoding="async" class="aligncenter wp-image-5847" src="https://www.ohmyfoodrecipes.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/03/beef-in-instant-pot-1024x684.jpg" alt="beef and sauce into instant pot" width="850" height="567" srcset="https://www.ohmyfoodrecipes.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/03/beef-in-instant-pot-1024x684.jpg 1024w, https://www.ohmyfoodrecipes.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/03/beef-in-instant-pot-500x334.jpg 500w, https://www.ohmyfoodrecipes.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/03/beef-in-instant-pot-768x513.jpg 768w, https://www.ohmyfoodrecipes.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/03/beef-in-instant-pot.jpg 1200w" sizes="(max-width: 850px) 100vw, 850px" data-pin-media="https://www.ohmyfoodrecipes.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/03/beef-in-instant-pot.jpg"></noscript></p>
<p>4. After the pressure release, add radish into instant pot. Then, close the lid and vent. Push manual button and adjust time for 15 minutes at high pressure and natural release.&nbsp;</p>
<p><img decoding="async" class="aligncenter wp-image-5844 perfmatters-lazy" src="data:image/svg+xml,%3Csvg%20xmlns=&#039;http://www.w3.org/2000/svg&#039;%20width=&#039;850&#039;%20height=&#039;567&#039;%20viewBox=&#039;0%200%20850%20567&#039;%3E%3C/svg%3E" alt="Green onion added into instant pot with Chinese beef brisket" width="850" height="567" data-pin-media="https://www.ohmyfoodrecipes.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/03/braised-beef-radish-instant-pot.jpg" data-src="https://www.ohmyfoodrecipes.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/03/braised-beef-radish-instant-pot-1024x684.jpg" data-srcset="https://www.ohmyfoodrecipes.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/03/braised-beef-radish-instant-pot-1024x684.jpg 1024w, https://www.ohmyfoodrecipes.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/03/braised-beef-radish-instant-pot-500x334.jpg 500w, https://www.ohmyfoodrecipes.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/03/braised-beef-radish-instant-pot-768x513.jpg 768w, https://www.ohmyfoodrecipes.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/03/braised-beef-radish-instant-pot.jpg 1200w" data-sizes="(max-width: 850px) 100vw, 850px" /><noscript><img decoding="async" class="aligncenter wp-image-5844" src="https://www.ohmyfoodrecipes.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/03/braised-beef-radish-instant-pot-1024x684.jpg" alt="Green onion added into instant pot with Chinese beef brisket" width="850" height="567" srcset="https://www.ohmyfoodrecipes.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/03/braised-beef-radish-instant-pot-1024x684.jpg 1024w, https://www.ohmyfoodrecipes.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/03/braised-beef-radish-instant-pot-500x334.jpg 500w, https://www.ohmyfoodrecipes.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/03/braised-beef-radish-instant-pot-768x513.jpg 768w, https://www.ohmyfoodrecipes.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/03/braised-beef-radish-instant-pot.jpg 1200w" sizes="(max-width: 850px) 100vw, 850px" data-pin-media="https://www.ohmyfoodrecipes.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/03/braised-beef-radish-instant-pot.jpg"></noscript></p>
<p>5. Add green onion and mix them will. You can use a <a href="https://amzn.to/2vVFdb7" target="_blank" rel="nofollow noopener noreferrer">strainer</a> to remove oil or fat. (If you want the sauce thicker, you can thicken the sauce by adding corn starch and water.)&nbsp;</p>
<p><img decoding="async" class="aligncenter wp-image-5845 perfmatters-lazy" src="data:image/svg+xml,%3Csvg%20xmlns=&#039;http://www.w3.org/2000/svg&#039;%20width=&#039;850&#039;%20height=&#039;567&#039;%20viewBox=&#039;0%200%20850%20567&#039;%3E%3C/svg%3E" alt="Aisan Chinese beef brisket and daikon in a brown clay pot" width="850" height="567" data-pin-media="https://www.ohmyfoodrecipes.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/03/brasied-beef-and-radish-horizontal.jpg" data-src="https://www.ohmyfoodrecipes.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/03/brasied-beef-and-radish-horizontal-1024x684.jpg" data-srcset="https://www.ohmyfoodrecipes.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/03/brasied-beef-and-radish-horizontal-1024x684.jpg 1024w, https://www.ohmyfoodrecipes.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/03/brasied-beef-and-radish-horizontal-500x334.jpg 500w, https://www.ohmyfoodrecipes.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/03/brasied-beef-and-radish-horizontal-768x513.jpg 768w, https://www.ohmyfoodrecipes.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/03/brasied-beef-and-radish-horizontal.jpg 1200w" data-sizes="(max-width: 850px) 100vw, 850px" /><noscript><img decoding="async" class="aligncenter wp-image-5845" src="https://www.ohmyfoodrecipes.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/03/brasied-beef-and-radish-horizontal-1024x684.jpg" alt="Aisan Chinese beef brisket and daikon in a brown clay pot" width="850" height="567" srcset="https://www.ohmyfoodrecipes.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/03/brasied-beef-and-radish-horizontal-1024x684.jpg 1024w, https://www.ohmyfoodrecipes.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/03/brasied-beef-and-radish-horizontal-500x334.jpg 500w, https://www.ohmyfoodrecipes.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/03/brasied-beef-and-radish-horizontal-768x513.jpg 768w, https://www.ohmyfoodrecipes.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/03/brasied-beef-and-radish-horizontal.jpg 1200w" sizes="(max-width: 850px) 100vw, 850px" data-pin-media="https://www.ohmyfoodrecipes.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/03/brasied-beef-and-radish-horizontal.jpg"></noscript></p>
<p class="p1">Enjoy this simple and tasty Cantonese style Asian beef stew recipe! Also, check out these <a href="https://www.ohmyfoodrecipes.com/soy-sauce-chicken/">soy sauce chicken</a>, <a href="https://www.ohmyfoodrecipes.com/beef-stew/">beef stew</a>&nbsp;and <a href="https://www.ohmyfoodrecipes.com/bbq-ribs/">BBQ pork</a>&nbsp;instant pot recipes.</p>
