			<p class="comment-author">
				<span class="comment-author-name">Tracy O.</span> <span class="says">says</span>			</p>

			<p class="comment-meta"><time class="comment-time">July 24, 2021 at 3:22 pm</time></p>		</header>

		<div class="comment-content">
			
			<p>Regular soy sauce. If you want the liquid darker color, you can add a little bit of dark soy sauce.</p>
		</div>

		
		
	</article>
	</li><!-- #comment-## -->
</ul><!-- .children -->
</li><!-- #comment-## -->
</ul><!-- .children -->
</li><!-- #comment-## -->

	<li class="comment even thread-odd thread-alt depth-1" id="comment-120">
	<article id="article-comment-120">

		
		<header class="comment-header">
			<p class="comment-author">
				<span class="comment-author-name">Laura Yee</span> <span class="says">says</span>			</p>

			<p class="comment-meta"><time class="comment-time">March 31, 2020 at 9:58 pm</time></p>		</header>

		<div class="comment-content">
			
			<p>I made this yesterday and was it was delicious ... and easy to make in the pressure cooker.  The stew is similar if not better as I remember from growing up in San Francisco Chinatown. I have brown slab sugar and used that instead of brown sugar. Glad I found your blog through a FB Asian Instant Pot group.</p>
		</div>

		<div class="comment-reply"><a rel="nofollow" class="comment-reply-link" href="#comment-120" data-commentid="120" data-postid="5841" data-belowelement="article-comment-120" data-respondelement="respond" data-replyto="Reply to Laura Yee" aria-label="Reply to Laura Yee">Reply</a></div>
		
	</article>
	<ul class="children">

	<li class="comment byuser comment-author-ohmyfoodrecipes bypostauthor odd alt depth-2" id="comment-121">
	<article id="article-comment-121">

		
		<header class="comment-header">
			<p class="comment-author">
				<span class="comment-author-name">Tracy O.</span> <span class="says">says</span>			</p>

			<p class="comment-meta"><time class="comment-time">March 31, 2020 at 10:09 pm</time></p>		</header>

		<div class="comment-content">
			
			<p>Thank you for your comment! Normally, I use rock sugar. Sometimes, I ran out of rock sugar I will use brown slab sugar. If I ran out both then I will use brown sugar, they turn out great as well.</p>
		</div>

		<div class="comment-reply"><a rel="nofollow" class="comment-reply-link" href="#comment-121" data-commentid="121" data-postid="5841" data-belowelement="article-comment-121" data-respondelement="respond" data-replyto="Reply to Tracy O." aria-label="Reply to Tracy O.">Reply</a></div>
		
	</article>
	</li><!-- #comment-## -->
</ul><!-- .children -->
</li><!-- #comment-## -->

	<li class="comment even thread-even depth-1" id="comment-117">
	<article id="article-comment-117">

		
		<header class="comment-header">
			<p class="comment-author">
				<span class="comment-author-name">Dorothy</span> <span class="says">says</span>			</p>

			<p class="comment-meta"><time class="comment-time">March 25, 2020 at 6:09 am</time></p>		</header>

		<div class="comment-content">
			
			<p>How do you adjust the cooking time if more meat is added?</p>
		</div>

		<div class="comment-reply"><a rel="nofollow" class="comment-reply-link" href="#comment-117" data-commentid="117" data-postid="5841" data-belowelement="article-comment-117" data-respondelement="respond" data-replyto="Reply to Dorothy" aria-label="Reply to Dorothy">Reply</a></div>
		
	</article>
	<ul class="children">

	<li class="comment byuser comment-author-ohmyfoodrecipes bypostauthor odd alt depth-2" id="comment-119">
	<article id="article-comment-119">

		
		<header class="comment-header">
			<p class="comment-author">
				<span class="comment-author-name">Tracy O.</span> <span class="says">says</span>			</p>

			<p class="comment-meta"><time class="comment-time">March 27, 2020 at 5:27 pm</time></p>		</header>

		<div class="comment-content">
			
			<p>It is the same amount of cooking time if you add more meat. If you worry, you can manual and adjust time to 50-60 minutes. Hope this help!</p>
		</div>

		<div class="comment-reply"><a rel="nofollow" class="comment-reply-link" href="#comment-119" data-commentid="119" data-postid="5841" data-belowelement="article-comment-119" data-respondelement="respond" data-replyto="Reply to Tracy O." aria-label="Reply to Tracy O.">Reply</a></div>
		
	</article>
	</li><!-- #comment-## -->
</ul><!-- .children -->
</li><!-- #comment-## -->
